        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16972",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "zh is the unicode definition for \"chinese\"...\n\nThe region code is added after the language.\nYou can refer to the ZF docu for how this works.\n\nzh_TW for example means chinese language, region taiwan.\n\nYou can already use this sort of locales with Zend_Locale and also with Zend_Translate.\nThere is nothing which has to be changed for this.\n\nBut wether the language nor the region include which script the user wants.\nThis has nothing to do with language or region.\n\nWe will not change the CLDR library as this is legal property of unicode. \n\nActually the best way for you is, to make two translations, one for trad, one for simple and assign them to two different locales. f.e. zh_TW = trad, zh_MO = simp...\n\nAs long as scripts are not part of the locale there is no way to do this the way you proposed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-26T06:17:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-26T06:17:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16973",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "But in ZF Zend_Translate docs it describes used only the language code for language selection.\nIn that case, can not recognize trad or simple language file to use.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-26T06:39:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-26T06:39:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16974",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You are able to define full locales for Zend_Translate.\n\n\"zh_TW\" or \"zh_CN\" is also possible as the abbreviated \"zh\".\nMostly it's enough to define only the language...\n\nFor example in german it's enough to define \"de\" because \"de_AT\" and \"de_DE\" use the same script.\n\nWhen you have a constallation as you described it, it would be best to use as the region as selection criteria.\nThis is already possible with Zend_Translate.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-26T09:11:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-26T09:11:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16981",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assigning to [~thomas]. Is this a non-issue, or what action should we take to remedy the problem, which remains a bit unclear to me?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-26T14:59:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-26T14:59:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16989",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Chen want to define something like this...\n\nZend_Locale(array('zh', 'Traditional'));\n\nBut this is not possible with cldr.\n\nActually the I18N core does not support to have one locale with multiple scripts defined.\nThe script is independend from the locale.\n\nHe has to define the region additionally to the language and make two translations, one for traditional and one for simplified as described in my post above.\n\nFor example... zh_CN (chinese-china) for traditional and zh_TW (chinese-taiwan) for simplified. He would have to make a selection for the user between simplified and traditional and redirect to the above specified locales. \n\nLocales do not include scripts.\nBut the description of the header of this issue is already possible.\n\nIn my eyes this is no issue for Zend_Translate nor for Zend_Locale.\nScripts are no locales... these are 2 seperated types of informations.\n\nI will wait a few days if the thing is clear for Chen... if no additional problems occur (the mentioned way from above should already work) I will close this issue as \"no issue\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-26T16:02:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-26T16:02:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16990",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{code}\n$trans = new Zend_Translate(\"gettext\", 'locale\\messages.mo', \"en\");\n$trans->addTranslation('locale\\messages.cn', \"zh\");\n$trans->addTranslation('locale\\messages.tw', \"zh\");\n{code}\n\nIf the language file use only language code 'zh' to define, then how does Zend_Translate know how to determine which language to use if remote user uses one of Chinese language ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-26T18:13:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-26T18:13:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16994",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As I said you have to use also the region...\n\n{code}\n$trans = new Zend_Translate(\"gettext\", 'locale\\messages.mo', \"en\");\n$trans->addTranslation('locale\\messages.cn', \"zh\");\n$trans->addTranslation('locale\\messages.tw', \"zh_TW\");\n{code}\n\nThis way \"zh_TW\" would be traditional.\n\"zh\" would be simplified.\n\nIf a messageid in traditional is not translated it would fall down to simplified.\nIf the messageid is also not translated in zh it would fall down to en and be displayed.\n\nIf you dont want to fall down from traditional to simplified just change \"zh\" to be \"zh_CN\"...\n{code}\n$trans = new Zend_Translate(\"gettext\", 'locale\\messages.mo', \"en\");\n$trans->addTranslation('locale\\messages.cn', \"zh_CN\");\n$trans->addTranslation('locale\\messages.tw', \"zh_TW\");\n{code}\n\nThis way if a messageid is not translated it falls always down to \"en\".\n\nHow the fallback mechanism works is described in the docu for Zend_Translate.\nHow Locales work is described  in the docu for Zend_Locale.\nAnd which locales exist is described in the last two chapters of Zend_Locale.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-27T01:04:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-27T01:04:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16995",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank you for your instruction.\nSorry for this mistake comment.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-27T02:06:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-27T02:06:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
